                    **Customer Segmentation Analysis**
Customer segmentation is a powerful marketing technique that involves dividing a customer base into distinct 
segments based on shared characteristics, behaviours, or demographics. 

Dataset
The dataset used for this analysis can be found on Kaggle's Marketing Analytics -  https://www.kaggle.com/code/analystoleksandra/marketing-analytics-customer-segmentation
It includes customer purchase records and relevant metrics such as the frequency of purchases, total spend, and recency of transactions.

**Conclusion:**
The average purchase value is 563.789213260762
The average Income is 51687.2587827808
Most customer are between the Age range 40-50 
Widow spends the highest amount on purchase and they are the most educated.
